    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel your<strong> potato[es]</strong> and chop them into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender, once done, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-lean-beef-cottage-pie-with-cheesy-sweet-potato-mash/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, reboil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail, and dice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-lean-beef-cottage-pie-with-cheesy-sweet-potato-mash/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong>, <strong>diced</strong> <strong>carrot </strong>and<strong> chopped garlic </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 5-6 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your<strong> beef stock mix</strong> and<strong> tomato paste</strong> in 250ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [325ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and stir in your <strong>Marmite</strong> \u2013 this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-lean-beef-cottage-pie-with-cheesy-sweet-potato-mash/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the vegetables have softened, increase the heat to high and add your <strong>mince </strong>to the pan<strong> </strong>then cook for 3-4 min or until browned, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Once the mince has browned, add the <strong>tomato stock </strong>to the pan</p><p>Season with a grind of<strong> black pepper</strong> and cook for 5 min or until slightly thickened and the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>mince mixture</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-lean-beef-cottage-pie-with-cheesy-sweet-potato-mash/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the mince mixture thickens, return the<strong> drained potatoes</strong> to a low heat with a small knob of <strong>butter </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Mash until smooth</p><p>Grate your <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-lean-beef-cottage-pie-with-cheesy-sweet-potato-mash/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mince mixture has thickened, transfer it to an<strong> oven-proof dish</strong></p><p>Top with the<strong> mashed potato </strong>and sprinkle over the <strong>grated cheese</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven for 15-20 min or until golden brown and bubbling \u2013 this is your <strong>cottage pie</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-lean-beef-cottage-pie-with-cheesy-sweet-potato-mash/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the cottage pie is cooking, reboil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>blanched peas</strong> to a pot, cover them with <strong>boiling water </strong>(just enough to cover them) with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 1 min or until they're warmed through</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-lean-beef-cottage-pie-with-cheesy-sweet-potato-mash/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> cottage pie</strong> with the <strong>peas </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Loved this recipe? Keep an eye out for it on the Everyday Favourites section of our menu.</span></strong></p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
